<div id="review_3345991098" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3345991098" />
    <a title="Scot Glasgow" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30014192-scot-glasgow"><img alt="Scot Glasgow" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590501938p2/30014192.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3345991098?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Scot Glasgow" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Scot Glasgow" href="/user/show/30014192-scot-glasgow">Scot Glasgow</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8242507-the-dragonbone-chair">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3345991098" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7215457183803358451">I thoroughly enjoyed this book from beginning to end. I understand the complaints regarding its pacing ... and much like other fantasy epics (especially book 1&apos;s) I simply don&apos;t care. Tad Williams is an exceptional writer with fantastic prose - his use of language adds considerably to my enjoyment of the narrative, in much the same way that Hobb and Rothfuss are able to transport me into their worlds and the lives of their characters with their beautiful writing.<br/><br/>By far my favorite character in t</span>
  <span id="freeText7215457183803358451" style="display:none">I thoroughly enjoyed this book from beginning to end. I understand the complaints regarding its pacing ... and much like other fantasy epics (especially book 1's) I simply don't care. Tad Williams is an exceptional writer with fantastic prose - his use of language adds considerably to my enjoyment of the narrative, in much the same way that Hobb and Rothfuss are able to transport me into their worlds and the lives of their characters with their beautiful writing.<br /><br />By far my favorite character in the story was the troll Binabik - his loyalty and friendship to the protagonist Simon was something I truly appreciated, and his backstory being slowly and methodically revealed was a pleasure to read.<br /><br />I'm excited to continue the series through at least the trilogy in the read-along with Mike's Book Reviews, and will likely pick up the sequel trilogy soon thereafter.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7215457183803358451" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
